observations.recommendation:
1. The General Services Officer together with the Municipal Engineer must conduct an inventory of local roads under the LGU’s jurisdiction. Provide a copy of the inventory reports to the accountant for proper accounting and reconciliation;
2. The municipal accountant shall reconcile the inventory report with those recorded in the registry of public infrastructure. Also, the accountant should strictly follow the accounting and reporting procedures provided under COA Circular No. 2015-008 on the valuation of these road asset networks; and
3. The local chief executive must monitor the compliance by the concerned officials with the above-mentioned circular.
